commitResults.messageBody:
For example, use List for ArrayList, and Map for HashMap.

This is considered good practice since it enables better maintainability, say, if we want to use LinkedList in place of ArrayList someday.

TreeSet is yet to be replaced since we make use of the first() and last() methods, which should not have been used for a Set ADT in the first place. We may want to factor those out as well some day.

This is primarily used for programmatically (not logically) impossible situations that the compiler is unable to diagnose. For example, the default case after we exhaust all possible cases in an enum.

Intended data flow:
... -> NusModsParser.getLessons -> Lesson[]

* Rethrow generalised GetTaskFailedException
* Invert condition to reduce nesting

* Correct asserted exception being thrown
* Make the test more defensive against failure, which can cause subsequent tests to falsely fail
